The construction of the South Stream pipeline in Bulgaria put the launch of one of the largest European energy projects, said the Gazprom board.
"Today's event is a milestone: The construction work on the Bulgarian section of the gas pipeline, which is the largest and most important project in Europe, have begun," said the chairman of Gazprom, Alexei Miller, in a statement on Thursday.
The project is a key element for the security of the entire European continent.
South Stream is meant for more diversity in Russia's export routes through Europe.
